    {
      "id": "9a437d4f_fc358246",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/config/pod-config-init.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 13,
      "message": "wondering the reason for the 1.1.1 tag and why you decided not  to use 1.1.0?  We don't really have a rule around this version number but I've been treating it as a major/minor release thing.  and this change is still part of a major release of 1.1.0 that we are all working on.  If say, these logging changes came in after all the 1.1.0 changes were done and tested I could see the use of 1.1.1 as tag.  If the reason is to enable independent testing of the config pod before merging then I would suggest tagging and pushing to a local (internal to your environment) nexus and test using that.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 131,
        "name": "Mandeep Khinda",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "Mandeep.Khinda@gmail.com",
        "username": "mkhinda"
      },
      "updated": "2017-09-05 17:54:33.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "9a437d4f_bc3ffa24",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/log/templates/all-services.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 1,
      "message": "Do you really NEED node ports for all 3 services?  We try to avoid using them for backend services that are not accessed by the end user of the ONAP platform.  Could you not get away with just having a NP for the kibana front end here?\n\nIf you do need them, then there has been some work put in to parameterize them using helm that you should align with.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 131,
        "name": "Mandeep Khinda",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "Mandeep.Khinda@gmail.com",
        "username": "mkhinda"
      },
      "updated": "2017-09-05 17:54:33.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "9a437d4f_fc0c6296",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/log/templates/elasticsearch-deployment.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 48,
      "message": "did you consider using a readinessProbe to allow K8s to detect when the service is really running?  i.e. port 9300 is open?\n\nThe same comment can be made for the other new deployment yamls",
      "author": {
